text: Saint-Leu-la-Forêt is a railway station located in the commune of Saint-Leu- la-Forêt (Val-d'Oise department), France. The station is served by Transilien H trains, on the line from Paris to Persan-Beaumont via Saint-Leu-la-Forêt. The daily number of passengers was between 2,500 and 7,500 in 2002.STIF - Atlas des transports publics en Île-de-France The station has 2 free parking lots with 118 and 168 places. Saint-Leu-la-Forêt is located on the line from Ermont-Eaubonne to Valmondois, that was opened in 1876. The line was electrified in 1970.La Vie du Rail magazine June 28, 1970 - Électrification de la gare de Montsoult-Maffliers.
